The paper proposes a technique for inputting topological signatures to deep neural networks for machine learning tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the experiments involve classification of 2D object shapes (cs.CV), social network graphs (cs.SI), and the use of persistent homology (cs.DS) and deep neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE, and cs.SI, in that order.
